Third-party components vendored or referenced
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This product bundles or depends on the following third-party software,
each under its own license:

  * OpenSSL 1.1.1w
      License: OpenSSL (Apache-style; dual with SSLeay)
      Source:  https://github.com/janbar/openssl-cmake
      Used:    crypto primitives (Ed25519, SHA-256, AES-256-GCM,
               EVP_PKEY API, PBKDF2)

  * Asio 1.30.2 (standalone)
      License: Boost Software License 1.0
      Source:  https://github.com/chriskohlhoff/asio
      Used:    networking (gossip + RPC servers)

  * nlohmann/json 3.11.3
      License: MIT
      Source:  https://github.com/nlohmann/json
      Used:    JSON serialization (config, RPC, snapshots, block JSON)

  * libsodium (via robinlinden/libsodium-cmake)
      License: ISC
      Source:  https://github.com/robinlinden/libsodium-cmake
      Used:    wallet binary primitives (ristretto255, Argon2id) for
               the OPAQUE adapter (A2 Phase 4+)

  * liboprf
      License: LGPL-3.0
      Source:  https://github.com/stef/liboprf
      Status:  declared in CMakeLists.txt under -DDETERM_VENDOR_OPRF=ON
               (default OFF; vendoring scaffolding only — see
               wallet/PHASE6_PORTING_NOTES.md). Not currently linked
               into shipped binaries.

